1. Using vi write your CV in the file mycv. Your CV should include your name, age, school, college, experience,...

[shimaa@localhost ~]$ gedit shimaaLab3
[shimaa@localhost ~]$ touch mycv
[shimaa@localhost ~]$ vi mycv
[shimaa@localhost solutionLab3]$ cat mycv
myName : shimaa abd el azim
age : 26
college : computer sciense

2. Open mycv file using vi command then: Without using arrows state how to:
a. Move the cursor down one line at time.
press on j

b. Move the cursor up one line at time.
press on k

c. Search for word age
/age

d. Step to line 5 (assuming that you are in line 1 and file is more than 5 lines).
5G

e. Delete the line you are on and line 5.
dd 5G dd

f. How to step to the end of line and change to writing mode in one-step.

A

